<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="names">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Names.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Myanmar</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">sekku-pan</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">English</emphasis>
: great bougainvillea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Native of Brazil. Cultivated elsewhere.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
Plant used for medicinal purposes (exact uses not given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordal, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="174" pageNumber="175" refId="B85" refString="Nordal, A, 1963. The Medicinal Plants and Crude Drugs of Burma. Hellstrom &amp; Nordahls Boktrykkeri, Oslo." title="The Medicinal Plants and Crude Drugs of Burma. Hellstrom &amp; Nordahls Boktrykkeri, Oslo." year="1963">Nordal 1963</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="128" pageNumber="129" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
Traditional practitioners in Mandsaur use the leaves for a variety of disorders, including the treatment of diarrhea and to reduce stomach acidity; the species is used elsewhere as follows- for cough and sore throat, a decoction of dried flowers (in water) is used for blood vessels and leucorrhea, a decoction of dried stems (in water) is used for hepatitis (
<bibRefCitation author="Edwin, E" journalOrPublisher="ARS Pharmaceutica" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" pagination="135 - 144" publicationUrl="http://farmacia.ugr.es/ars/articulo.php?384" refId="B35" refString="Edwin, E, Sheeja, E, Toppo, E, Tiwari, V, Dutt, KR, 2007. Anti-diarrhoeal, anti-ulcer and antimicrobial activities of leaves of Bougainvillea glabra Choisy. ARS Pharmaceutica 48 (2): 135 - 144, http://farmacia.ugr.es/ars/articulo.php?384" title="Anti-diarrhoeal, anti-ulcer and antimicrobial activities of leaves of Bougainvillea glabra Choisy." url="http://farmacia.ugr.es/ars/articulo.php?384" volume="48" year="2007">Edwin et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
